    "1. **Autonomous, Multi-Fidelity Budget Allocation Policies.** While the worked example statically allocates feedback budgets across proxy and simulation stages, future AI architects require learned, dynamic policies to optimally distribute these budgets across sprawling design spaces. Research must define the state schemas and multi-fidelity training environments necessary to train reinforcement learning agents that autonomously decide when to escalate, reject, or request stronger checks, while strictly adhering to the commitment boundaries formalized in @pri-honest-evidence.\n",
