    "2. **Proactive Detection of Proxy Mirage and Architectural Blind Spots.** As demonstrated during escalation, cheap analytical proxies often exhibit catastrophic blind spots, such as ignoring interface taxes or data movement. Rather than passively waiting for expensive simulation to catch these inversions, research must develop predictive methods and formal verification techniques capable of structurally analyzing proxy models. The goal is to mathematically bound the risk of proxy mismatch and proactively identify when a proxy is actively misleading before expending scarce cycle-level simulation budgets.\n",
